## 6. Verified Brand Facts — Džiugas / Žemaitijos Pienas

Sources: [zpienas.lt](https://www.zpienas.lt/dziugas/), [dziugashouse.lt](https://dziugashouse.lt/en/about-us/), [Dairy Industries Intl.](https://www.dairyindustries.com/news/32471/), [Nasdaq Baltic H1 2025 Report](https://attachment.news.eu.nasdaq.com/)

### Identity
- **Brand:** Džiugas® (hard cheese)
- **Parent:** Žemaitijos Pienas AB, Nasdaq Vilnius listed, 1,300+ employees
- **Founded:** 1924, Telšiai, Samogitia, Lithuania
- **Name origin:** Lithuanian folklore — warrior giant Džiugas who protected Samogitia, married Austelė, pressed cheese on wedding night per Samogitian tradition
- **Godparents:** President Valdas Adamkus and Alma Adamkienė (2010)

### Product
- **Ingredients (only 4):** Summer milk from free-grazing Samogitian cows, starter culture, non-animal rennet, salt
- **Properties:** Lactose-free, vegetarian-friendly, no artificial colorings/preservatives, rich in calcium, phosphorus, protein
- **Aging:** 12–120 months, wheels turned every 3 days, aged to M. K. Čiurlionis and Oginskis symphonies
- **Product tiers (8):**
  - Mild (12mo), Piquant (18mo), Delicate (24mo), Gourmet (36mo)
  - Luxurious (48mo), Exclusive (60mo), Special Aged (100mo), Extra Aged (120mo)

### Recognition
- **Awards:** 90+ international (DLG, Crystal Taste, Superior Taste Award, Anuga, Premio Roma)
- **Protection:** EU PGI since 2019, Japan GI proposed August 2025
- **Exports:** 40+ countries, "Džiugas Days" in 12+ markets (2025)
- **Post-2022:** Russia/Belarus/China markets closed; sales redirected to EU, UK, Japan, Uzbekistan, Croatia

### Production Stages (from dziugashouse.lt)
1. Shaping in round moulds → cheese press
2. "Gentle hands" — placed in rings, warm environment, hand-turned
3. Brine bath
4. Aging cellars — turned every 3 days for weeks
5. Long ripening — fermentation, biochemical changes, calcium crystal formation

